## 3. Data Flow
The system follows a synchronous request-response flow:

1.  **Request:** A client sends an HTTP request (e.g., `GET /peces/temporada?zona=Yucatan`).
2.  **Controller:** [PezController](file:///c:/Users/cesar/IdeaProjects/api-pesca-merida/src/main/java/com/pescayucatan/api_pesca_merida/controller/PezController.java#12-45) captures the `zona` parameter and delegates to [PezService](file:///c:/Users/cesar/IdeaProjects/api-pesca-merida/src/main/java/com/pescayucatan/api_pesca_merida/service/PezService.java#12-54).
3.  **Service:** [PezService](file:///c:/Users/cesar/IdeaProjects/api-pesca-merida/src/main/java/com/pescayucatan/api_pesca_merida/service/PezService.java#12-54) converts the string to a `ZonaPesca` enum via [forValue()](file:///c:/Users/cesar/IdeaProjects/api-pesca-merida/src/main/java/com/pescayucatan/api_pesca_merida/enums/ZonaPesca.java#23-32). It validates the input and calls the repository.
4.  **Repository:** [PezRepository](file:///c:/Users/cesar/IdeaProjects/api-pesca-merida/src/main/java/com/pescayucatan/api_pesca_merida/repository/PezRepository.java#10-15) executes a query against the underlying database.
5.  **Return Path:** Data (or an Exception) flows back through the Service to the Controller, which returns a JSON response (or structured error via `GlobalExceptionHandler`).

